## Description
The **Email template&nbsp;**resource&nbsp;allows to manage email assets. You can use this resource in workflow tasks that deliver emails.

## Additional creation parameters
None.

## Resource editor
None.

## Release parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Field

Description

**File**

HTML file representing the email template

For example:&nbsp;[Example-Doxee-Convention-Email.html](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/download/attachments/102509780/Example-Doxee-Convention-Email.html?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1645692830876&amp;api=v2)

**Summary**

Brief description of the release

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Release**

Select a release of the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Tenant**

Select the&nbsp;tenant&nbsp;on which you want to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**From**

**Name**

*(optional)&nbsp;*Name that will be displayed in the "From" field of the emails&nbsp;

**Address**

Email address to be used as sender's "From" address&nbsp;

**Reply**

**Name**

*(optional)&nbsp;*Name that will be displayed when the email recipient replies to the email

**Address**

*(optional)&nbsp;*Email address to be used when replying to the email

**Tracking**

**Analytics**

Enable Analytics tracking.

> Tip

Click **Publish **to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
